# =============================================================================
# .gitignore for Pensees
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Repo is currently greenfield (README-only). Sections below are intentionally
# broad so the ignore set stays useful as the codebase grows. Prune unused
# language sections later once the tech stack solidifies.
#
# IMPORTANT: The DevolaFlow agent workspace and compiled outputs are ignored
# wholesale here (per W1.T2 acceptance criteria). Do NOT re-introduce the
# legacy `.local/*` whitelist (with `!.local/memory/specs/**` negations) that
# earlier scaffold versions emitted — that defeats the "no untracked .local
# noise" goal the operator chose under commit-strategy option C.
# =============================================================================

# DevolaFlow agent workspace (internal state — never commit)
# Everything under .local/ is per-agent scratch / task / memory / handoff
# state. It must stay local; do not whitelist subpaths. The sibling .rules/
# directory holds project source-of-truth rule files (*.mdc, compile-config.
# yaml) and IS tracked; only the compile cache (.compile-hashes.json) is
# ignored.
.local/

# DevolaFlow compiled outputs (regenerated by devola-init / rule compiler)
# These are derived from .rules/*.mdc sources. Re-running the compiler
# reproduces them exactly, so they should not pollute git history.
/AGENTS.md
.cursor/rules/
.rules/.compile-hashes.json

# Local IDE / agent operator state (per-machine, per-session — never share)
# .cursor/plans/ holds operator-authored IDE plans; .agent-worker-logs/ holds
# transient agent worker logs. Both are session-scoped and should not pollute
# fresh clones of the repo.
.cursor/plans/
.agent-worker-logs/

# OS / editor
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.idea/
.vscode/
# If the team later wants to share editor settings, un-ignore specific files
# here (example):
# !.vscode/settings.json
# !.vscode/extensions.json
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# Language-agnostic build artifacts
# Trim the sections below once the project's actual stack is known.

# --- Python ---
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.tox/
*.egg-info/
*.egg
dist/
build/
.venv/
venv/
env/
ENV/

# --- Node / JS / TS ---
node_modules/
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log
pnpm-debug.log*
.next/
.nuxt/
.turbo/
.parcel-cache/
.cache/

# --- Rust ---
target/
Cargo.lock.bak

# --- Go ---
vendor/
*.test
*.out

# --- Java / JVM ---
*.class
*.jar

# Logs / temp / env
*.log
logs/
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
*.tmp
*.temp
coverage/
.coverage
.coverage.*
htmlcov/
